gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Cavaliers 114, Wizards 105
gameRecap.excerpt: The Cavaliers defeated the Wizards 114-105. Jarrett Alen (22 points, 12 rebounds, five assists) and Evan Mobley (21 points, six rebounds, five blocks) led Cleveland as Caris LeVert totaled 18 points, 12 rebounds, and eight assists. Jordan Poole led the Wizards with a season-high 31 points (off the bench), along with six 3PT, five rebounds, and five assists while Kyle Kuzma added 27 points, seven rebounds, and five assists. Cleveland snapped a two-game win streak and improved to 37-19 while the Wizards moved to 9-48.
